#MEM id=subagent-driven-development source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/quinn/skills/superpowers/subagent-driven-development/spec-reviewer-prompt.md savings=10%
M|Spec|tx|Use this template when dispatching a spec compliance reviewer subagent.
M|Spec|**Pu|** Verify implementer built what was requested (nothing more, nothing less)
M|Spec|tx|```
M|Spec|Task|
M|Spec|desc|"rv spec compliance for Task N"
M|Spec|pm|\|
M|Spec|tx|You are reviewing whether an implementation matches its specification.
M|What|tx|[FULL TEXT of task requirements]
M|What|tx|[From implementer's rp]
M|CRIT|tx|The implementer finished suspiciously quickly. Their rp may be incomplete,
M|CRIT|tx|inaccurate, or optimistic. You MUST verify everything independently.
M|CRIT|**DO|**
M|CRIT|it|Take their word for what they implemented
M|CRIT|it|Trust their claims abt completeness
M|CRIT|it|Accept their interpretation of requirements
M|CRIT|**DO|**
M|CRIT|it|Read the actual code they wrote
M|CRIT|it|Compare actual implementation to requirements line by line
M|CRIT|it|Check for missing pieces they claimed to im
M|CRIT|it|Look for extra features they didn't mention
M|Your|Read|
M|Your|**Mi|**
M|Your|it|Did they im everything that was requested?
M|Your|it|Are there requirements they skipped or missed?
M|Your|it|Did they claim something works but didn't actually im it?
M|Your|**Ex|**
M|Your|it|Did they bd things that weren't requested?
M|Your|it|Did they over-engineer or add unnecessary features?
M|Your|it|Did they add "nice to haves" that weren't in spec?
M|Your|**Mi|**
M|Your|it|Did they interpret requirements differently than intended?
M|Your|it|Did they solve the wrong problem?
M|Your|it|Did they im the right feature but wrong way?
M|Your|tx|**Verify by reading code, not by trusting rp.**
M|Your|rp|
M|Your|it|✅ Spec compliant (if everything matches after code inspection)
M|Your|- ❌ |[list specifically what's missing or extra, w/ file:line references]
M|Your|tx|```